        <preface>
            <p class="important">REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA</p>
            <p class="important">MINUTES OF PROCEEDINGS OF NATIONAL ASSEMBLY</p>
            <p class="important">THURSDAY, 25 AUGUST 2005</p>
        </preface>
        <maincontent>
            <list id="list1">
                <item id="item001">
                    <p>The House met at 14:02.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item002">
                    <p>The Deputy Speaker took the Chair and requested members to observe a moment
                        of silence for prayers or meditation.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item003">
                    <p><recordedTime time="14:03:00" /> Notices of motion.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item004">
                    <p><recordedTime time="14:04:00" /> The Chief Whip of the Majority Party moved:
                        That the House resolves that—</p>
                    <list id="list2">
                        <item id="item004-item001">
                            <p>in terms of <ref href="/act/1998/20_en.xml#sect02-art01">section 2(1)
                                    of the Remuneration of Public Office Bearers Act, 1998 (Act No
                                    20 of 1998)</ref>, and having due regard to the criteria listed
                                in that subsection, the salary and motor vehicle allowance payable
                                to the President of the Republic of South Africa be determined at
                                eight hundred and thirty seven thousand eight hundred and ninety
                                nine rand and thirty five cents (R837 899.35) and two hundred and
                                seventy nine thousand two hundred and ninety nine rand, seventy
                                cents (R279 299.70) per annum, respectively, with effect from 1
                                April 2005; and</p>
                        </item>
                        <item id="item004-item002">
                            <p>in terms of <ref href="/act/1998/20_en.xml#sect02-art02">section 2(2)
                                    of the said Act</ref>, the amount of forty thousand rand (R40
                                000) per annum be determined as that portion of the remuneration of
                                the President to which <ref
                                    href="/act/1962/58_en.xml#sect08-art01-cla04">section 8(1)(d) of
                                    the Income Tax Act, 1962 (Act No 58 of 1962)</ref>, shall
                            apply.</p>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                    <p>Agreed to.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item005">
                    <p><recordedTime time="14:05:00" /> Members’ statements.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item006">
                    <p>FIRST ORDER <recordedTime time="14:40:00" /></p>
                    <p>Second Reading Debate—<ref href="/bill/2005/75_en.xml">South African Abattoir
                            Corporation Act Repeal Bill [B 21—2005] (National Assembly—sec
                        75)</ref>.</p>
                    <p>There was no debate.</p>
                    <p>Bill read a second time.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item007">
                    <p>SECOND ORDER <recordedTime time="14:41:00" /></p>
                    <p>Consideration of <ref href="/report/CommitteeSafetySecurity/2005/0824_en.xml"
                            >Report of Portfolio Committee on Safety and Security
                            (Announcements,Tablings and Committee Reports, 24 August 2005, p
                                1687—<b>Independent Complaints Directorate</b>)</ref>.</p>
                    <p>Debate concluded.</p>
                    <p>The Deputy Chief Whip of the Majority Party moved: That the Report be
                        adopted.</p>
                    <p>Motion agreed to.</p>
                    <p>Report accordingly adopted.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item008">
                    <p>THIRD ORDER <recordedTime time="15:21:00" /></p>
                    <p>Consideration of request for approval by Parliament of <b>Statute of the
                            Centre for Science and Technology of the Non-Aligned Movement and Other
                            Developing Countries</b>, in terms of <ref
                            href="/constitution/en.xml#sec231-art2">section 231(2) of the
                            Constitution</ref> (Report of Portfolio Committee on Science and
                        Technology, see <ref href="/tablings/2005/0623_en.xml">Announcements,
                            Tablings and Committee Reports, 23 June 2005, p 1332</ref>). Mr E N N
                        Ngcobo, as chairperson of the Committee, introduced the Report.</p>
                    <p>There was no debate.</p>
                    <p><b>Statute of the Centre for Science and Technology of the Non-Aligned
                            Movement and Other Developing Countries</b> approved.</p>
                </item>
                <item id="item009">
                    <p>The House adjourned at 15:25.</p>
                </item>
